The paper deals with the design of online algorithms for stochastic combinatorial problems, which are typically studied in the subfield of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and online algorithms (cs.DS). The use of prophet inequalities is a common technique in both these subfields. The paper also involves the design of optimal algorithms, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the study of matroids, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and optimization (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT).
